==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shampoo
<hw>Sham*poo"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Shampooed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Shampooing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>ch⟦amac⟧mpn⟦amac⟧</ets> to press, to squeeze.]</ety>
<altsp>[Writing also <asp>champoo</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
press or knead the whole surface of the body of (a person), and at the
same time to stretch the limbs and joints, in connection with the hot
bath.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To wash throughly and rub the head of (a person),
with the fingers, using either soap, or a soapy preparation, for the
more thorough cleansing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shampoo</ent>⟦br⟧

